::Prowl::

Prowl frowns as Iron Raptor changes course, looking at the pod as 
they come up to it. He jumps off her back, walking to it to examine 
it.

"Its a blank," he finally says a bit dissapointed, "No spark.."


--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, "Megan Solmonson" <tmrattrap@h...> wrote:
> * Iron Raptor could feel the air being pulled into her lungs and 
then pushed 
> out in one fluid breath, only finding herself take in two breaths 
in one 
> minute.
> Which was great for what she was going to use this mode for if she 
ever 
> learned how to master it.
> 
> She felt Prowls grip tighten on her neck as she sped up, keeping 
her eyes 
> ahead of her and the only sound being that of her feet pounding in 
the 
> grasses.
> But then her keen eyes see the same glint of metal which Prowls 
had, 
> everything around her seeming to suddenly go slow-motion as she 
turns her 
> eyes towards the glint, getting a full view of the stasis pod 
despite her 
> speed.
> Then, everything was whizzing by again.
> But by then she had located the pod and changed course. Iron Raptor 
> eventually slowed and stopped a few feet away from the pod, then 
looking 
> around a bit and walking towards it with her head low.
> There seemed to be no life in this pod at all, also wondering what 
Prowl 
> thought of this too.*
